.TH SBT 1 "2026-05-01" "backup-utils 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sbt \- simple backup tool: directory sync and ISO archive
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sbt sync
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.I SRCDIR
.I DSTDIR
.PP
.B sbt archive
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.I SRCDIR
.I DSTDIR
.PP
.B sbt
.I COMMAND
.B \-\-help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sbt
is a backup utility with two subcommands:
.B sync
for incremental directory snapshots and
.B archive
for ISO image creation.
.SS sbt sync
Backs up
.I SRCDIR
into a timestamped snapshot directory under
.IR DSTDIR .
Snapshot directories are named
.BI backup- YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS \fR.
.PP
By default an incremental backup is performed: the most recent
.BI backup- *
directory found in
.I DSTDIR
is used as the
.B \-\-link\-dest
reference so that unchanged files are stored as hardlinks rather than copies.
Each snapshot therefore appears complete while consuming only the space of
the changed files.
If no prior snapshot exists, or if
.B \-\-full
is given, a full backup is performed instead.
.SS sbt archive
Produces an ISO 9660 image from the contents of
.I SRCDIR
via
.BR mkisofs (1).
The output file is written to
.I DSTDIR
as
.IB VOLNAME .iso
(where
.I VOLNAME
defaults to the name of
.I SRCDIR
converted to uppercase).
.I DSTDIR
is created automatically if it does not exist.
Joliet and Rock Ridge extensions are enabled so the image is readable on
both Windows and UNIX-like systems without filename mangling.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.SS sbt sync
.TP
.I SRCDIR
Path to the directory to back up.
.TP
.I DSTDIR
Absolute path to the directory that will hold all snapshots.
.SS sbt archive
.TP
.I SRCDIR
Path to the source directory whose contents will be packed into the image.
.TP
.I DSTDIR
Directory where the output
.I .iso
file will be written.
Created automatically if it does not exist.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS sbt sync
.TP
.BR \-\-full " / " \-\-no\-full
Force a full backup even when a prior snapshot exists.
Default:
.BR \-\-no\-full .
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show a usage summary and exit.
.SS sbt archive
.TP
.BI \-\-volname " VOLNAME"
Volume identifier embedded in the image header and used as the base name of
the output file
.RI ( VOLNAME .iso ).
Defaults to the name of
.I SRCDIR
converted to uppercase.
Must consist solely of uppercase letters
.RB ( A \(enZ ),
digits
.RB ( 0 \(en9 ),
and underscores
.RB ( _ ),
with a maximum of 32 characters (ISO 9660 restrictions).
.TP
.BI \-\-pubname " PUBNAME"
Publisher string embedded in the image header.
Optional.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show a usage summary and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
A subprocess
.RB ( rsync (1)
or
.BR mkisofs (1))
returned an error, or a validation check failed (missing source directory,
invalid volume name, output file already exists).
.TP
.B 2
Invalid or missing arguments (Typer usage error).
.SH EXAMPLES
Incremental backup of
.I /home/alice
into
.IR /mnt/nas/backups :
.PP
.RS
.EX
sbt sync /home/alice /mnt/nas/backups
# creates /mnt/nas/backups/backup-20260501-120000
# unchanged files are hardlinks to the prior snapshot
.EE
.RE
.PP
Force a full backup regardless of existing snapshots:
.PP
.RS
.EX
sbt sync --full /home/alice /mnt/nas/backups
.EE
.RE
.PP
Create
.I DOCS.iso
from
.I /data/docs
in
.IR /mnt/iso
(the source directory name is automatically uppercased):
.PP
.RS
.EX
sbt archive /data/docs /mnt/iso
.EE
.RE
.PP
Override the volume name and set a publisher:
.PP
.RS
.EX
sbt archive /data/docs /mnt/iso --volname DOCS --pubname "ACME Corp"
.EE
.RE
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.B sbt sync
requires
.BR rsync (1).
.PP
.B sbt archive
requires
.BR mkisofs (1)
(provided by the
.B genisoimage
package on Debian/Ubuntu).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rsync (1),
.BR mkisofs (1),
.BR genisoimage (1),
.BR isoinfo (1)
.SH AUTHORS
jimyoshida
